🚗 BRTA Service Management System

This project is a web-based platform I built to make the Bangladesh Road Transport Authority (BRTA) services more digital and efficient.
It includes both user and admin panels for managing license applications, road permits, accident reports, and driving appointment bookings — all in one place.

⚙️ Tech Stack

Frontend: HTML, CSS

Backend: PHP

Database: MySQL (phpMyAdmin)

Tools Used: VS Code, XAMPP, Apache Server

🚀 Features

User and Admin Panels:
I designed and developed separate panels for users and admins to make the system more organized and user-friendly.

License Application Management:
Users can apply for licenses, and admins can review and approve applications through an approval workflow.

Road Permit & Accident Reporting:
Added online forms for users to apply for road permits or submit accident reports.

Appointment Booking:
Implemented a simple appointment booking system for driving lessons or tests.

Admin Dashboard:
Created a complete admin dashboard to view service requests, approvals, and reports all in one view.

CRUD Operations:
Integrated full Create, Read, Update, and Delete features for managing user data and applications efficiently.


🛠️ How to Run Locally

Install XAMPP (for Apache and MySQL).

Start both Apache and MySQL from the XAMPP Control Panel.

Copy this project folder into:

C:\xampp\htdocs\


Open your browser and go to:

http://localhost/BRTA_Project/


Open phpMyAdmin, create a database (for example: brta_db) and import the .sql file from the database folder.
